<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Adventure_game&amp;action=edit&amp;section=23" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.ifreviews.org/" class="external text" title="http://www.ifreviews.org/" rel="nofollow">IFReviews Organization</a>, huge repository for text adventure game reviews written and rated by Interactive Fiction community players and members.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.atariarchives.org/adventure/" class="external text" title="http://www.atariarchives.org/adventure/" rel="nofollow">"Creating Adventure Games on Your Computer"</a> a 1983 programming manual by <a href="/wiki/Tim_Hartnell" title="Tim Hartnell">Tim Hartnell</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.adventureclassicgaming.com/index.php/site/features/105/" class="external text" title="http://www.adventureclassicgaming.com/index.php/site/features/105/" rel="nofollow">"Defining the ideal adventure game" article by David Tanguay (1999)</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.strangehorizons.com/2008/20080804/newheiser-a.shtml" class="external text" title="http://www.strangehorizons.com/2008/20080804/newheiser-a.shtml" rel="nofollow">"Searching under the rug", an article on adventure game puzzles and interfaces</a></li>
<li><a href="http://adventure.if-legends.org/" class="external text" title="http://adventure.if-legends.org/" rel="nofollow">Massive database of adventure games</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.GameBoomers.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.GameBoomers.com/" rel="nofollow">GameBoomers</a> walkthroughs, reviews, the latest info on Adventure Games.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.springbringer.com/fantasya/" class="external text" title="http://www.springbringer.com/fantasya/" rel="nofollow">Fantasy Adventures</a> - Classic adventure computer game museum</li>
<li><a href="http://scicommunity.com" class="external text" title="http://scicommunity.com" rel="nofollow">SCI Community</a> - Community based on making adventure games using Sierra's Creative Interpreter</li>
<li><a href="http://www.justadventure.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.justadventure.com/" rel="nofollow">Just Adventure+</a>, a repository for reviews and walkthroughs</li>
<li><a href="http://www.mysterymanor.net/" class="external text" title="http://www.mysterymanor.net/" rel="nofollow">Mystery Manor</a> - site dedicated to adventure games, with lots content such as walkthroughs, music, screenshots, and more.</li>
<li><a href="http://adventurepoint.co.uk/" class="external text" title="http://adventurepoint.co.uk/" rel="nofollow">Adventure Point</a> - An extremely useful resource for getting info on over 1200 graphic and text adventure games. Each graphic adventure in the extensive database has its own page and includes screenshots, a brief synopsis of what the game is like, plus a star rating. One novel approach involves listing adventure games by sub-category; puzzle, story, history, educational .... -type game, etc..</li>
</ul>
